headline: Alcoa Stock Sinks on Downgrade. J.P. Morgan Is Picking Copper Over Aluminum.
summary: The prices of both aluminum and copper surged in 2025, but copper is the clear winner in the months ahead,  J.P. Morgan  says.  J.P. Morgan downgraded shares of Alcoa to Underweight from Neutral in a research note Thursday, though it lifted its target for the price to $50 from $45.  Shares of Alcoa, which reports its quarterly earnings on Jan. 22, tumbled 3.7% to $60.45 on Thursday.

headline: Freeport-McMoRan Up 30% in 3 Months: Buy, Sell or Hold the Stock?
summary: FCX shares have surged 30% in three months, fueled by record copper prices, tightening supply concerns and strong demand from key global markets.
